description:
Wildlife: Episode 1 - Tiger, Lion, Leopard & Jaguar - The Four Big Cats | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'Wildlife - Episode 2: Crocodiles, Alligators, Caimans & Gharials' here: https://youtu.be/LUtg1qufIV0
 
Tigers, Lions, Leopards and Jaguars  the four big cats that can roar. This documentary takes you into the domains of the worlds largest felines to discover more about these magnificent carnivores and their fascinating lives. Travel the wilds of Africa, Asia and the Americas to watch these Apex Predators in action. While they share common features such as sharp claws, long tails and sleek, flexible bodies, each type of Big Cat has their own distinct set of attributes and behaviors, such as the famous stripes on a Tigers coat, the attractive rosettes spotting a Leopards fur and how Lions are social felines, living in groups called Prides. Let Big Cats astound you with their raw power, natural agility, cunning stealth and undeniable presence  qualities that have earned these formidable creatures global admiration for centuries.

You will see fascinating shots from the deep seas and up in the air, capturing great stories and pictures from everything our beautiful and interesting planet has to offer. 

Enjoy stories about nature, wildlife, culture, people, history and more to come.
